# No inline CSS in HTML

Never put `<style>` blocks inside HTML files. Always use external `.css` files included via `<link>`.

- Shared styles go in the root `style.css`
- Page-specific styles go in a `style.css` in the same directory as the HTML
- Theme variants use a descriptive name like `style-dark.css`

```html
<!-- BAD -->
<style>
    .my-class { color: red; }
</style>

<!-- GOOD -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
```
